Installing from sources

   1. Unpack asyscon source package
   2. Go to asyscon folder and type "phpize && ./configure && make && make install"
   3. Make sure you have extension=asyscon.so in your php.ini
   4. Add configuration lines to your php.ini to use the extension

Compiling Asyscon into PHP

   1. Unpack asyscon source package to $PHP_SOURCE_DIR/ext/asyscon
   2. In php source root directory run commands: "rm configure && ./buildconf --force"
   3. Configure PHP with command "./configure --with-asyscon"
   4. Run make && make install
   5. Add configuration lines to your php.ini to use the extension

